<template><div><h1 id="guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-presets" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-presets"><span><font color=#f0b6d5>Guide to Town of Host: Enhanced - <font color=#ebd326>Presets</font></font></span></a></h1>
<p>Presets are different saves of your settings. You can save your favorite settings as presets and load them later. You can also download presets shared by others.</p>
<p>For some User Submitted Presets, visit the <RouteLink to="/guides/usc/Presets.html">Presets</RouteLink> Page.</p>
<h2 id="how-do-you-use-someone-else-s-preset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#how-do-you-use-someone-else-s-preset"><span><font color=#f0b6d5>How do you use someone else's <font color=#ebd326>Preset</font>?</font></span></a></h2>
<h3 id="step-1-download-rename-preset-file" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-1-download-rename-preset-file"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 1:</font> Download + Rename Preset File</font></span></a></h3>
<p>If you want to use a preset that you've downloaded, make sure the file is renamed to <code v-pre>Options.json</code> before using it, if it isn't already. (If you do not have <code v-pre>File name extensions</code> marked on the <code v-pre>View</code> Tab, you only need to rename it to <code v-pre>Options</code>.)</p>
<h3 id="step-2-put-options-json-in-savedata-folder" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-2-put-options-json-in-savedata-folder"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 2:</font> Put Options.json in SaveData folder</font></span></a></h3>
<p>You have to put the file in the following directory: <code v-pre>...\Among Us\TOHE-DATA\SaveData</code> for it to work. (If you cannot locate <code v-pre>TOHE-DATA\SaveData</code>, try enabling <code v-pre>Hidden items</code> on the <code v-pre>View</code> Tab!)</p>
<h3 id="step-3-select-preset-in-tohe" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-3-select-preset-in-tohe"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 3:</font> Select Preset in TOHE</font></span></a></h3>
<p>Make sure you have the Preset selected in your System Settings, and play!</p>
<h4 id="you-have-successfully-downloaded-and-set-up-a-preset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#you-have-successfully-downloaded-and-set-up-a-preset"><span>You have successfully downloaded and set-up a Preset!</span></a></h4>
<h2 id="how-do-you-share-your-own-preset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#how-do-you-share-your-own-preset"><span><font color=#f0b6d5>How do you share your own <font color=#ebd326>Preset</font>?</font></span></a></h2>
<h3 id="step-1-locate-your-savedata-folder" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-1-locate-your-savedata-folder"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 1:</font> Locate your SaveData folder</font></span></a></h3>
<p>You can find this folder at the following directory: <code v-pre>...\Among Us\TOHE-DATA\SaveData</code>. (If you cannot locate <code v-pre>TOHE-DATA\SaveData</code>, try enabling <code v-pre>Hidden items</code> on the <code v-pre>View</code> Tab!)</p>
<h3 id="step-2-copy-options-json" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-2-copy-options-json"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 2:</font> Copy Options.json</font></span></a></h3>
<p>Copy the <code v-pre>Options.json</code> file from the <code v-pre>SaveData</code> folder, and paste it somewhere that you'll remember it, like the desktop.</p>
<h3 id="step-3-rename-options-json" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-3-rename-options-json"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 3:</font> Rename Options.json</font></span></a></h3>
<p>Rename your <code v-pre>Options.json</code> to whatever you want. John made a chaotic preset, he could name it <code v-pre>JohnsChaosPreset.json</code>, because it is <i>his</i> Preset, &amp; it tells people how it's <i>chaotic</i>.</p>
<h3 id="step-4-share-your-preset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-4-share-your-preset"><span><font color=#f0b6d5><font color=#ebd326>Step 4:</font> Share your Preset!</font></span></a></h3>
<p>There are a few ways to do this, they are the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Send the File Directly: Simply send the preset file to your friends so they can easily use it.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Submit for Public Sharing To have your preset featured, create a post in the <code v-pre>#website-feedback</code> channel of our Discord. Your preset will have a chance to be added to the User Submitted Presets page!</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h4 id="you-have-successfully-copied-and-shared-a-preset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#you-have-successfully-copied-and-shared-a-preset"><span>You have successfully copied and shared a Preset!</span></a></h4>
<h3 id="now-that-you-are-familiar-with-presets-you-should-learn-how-you-can-customize-your-lobbies-to-make-them-stand-out" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#now-that-you-are-familiar-with-presets-you-should-learn-how-you-can-customize-your-lobbies-to-make-them-stand-out"><span>Now that you are familiar with Presets, you should learn how you can customize your lobbies, to make them stand out!</span></a></h3>
</div></template>


